Definition.WordDefinition:
Two-sided \Two"-sid`ed\, a. 1. Having two sides only; hence, double-faced; hypocritical. [1913 Webster]
2. (Biol.) Symmetrical. [1913 Webster]

two-sided adj 1: capable of being reversed or used with either side out; "a reversible jacket" [syn: {reversible}] [ant: {nonreversible}] 2: having two sides or parts [syn: {bilateral}] [ant: {unilateral}, {multilateral}]
